      "source": [
        "## 1D Array Slicing"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d252a63b"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Define the array we will use for slicing examples\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "arr = np.arange(10)\n",
        "print(f\"Original array: {arr}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "d4929610"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Basic Slicing: `arr[start:end]`\n",
        "\n",
        "This extracts a portion of the array from `start` index up to (but not including) the `end` index."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "4f2429ad"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Get elements from index 2 to 5 (exclusive of index 5)\n",
        "slice_basic = arr[2:5]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[2:5] = {slice_basic}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get elements from the beginning up to index 4\n",
        "slice_from_start = arr[:5]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[:5] = {slice_from_start}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get elements from index 6 to the end\n",
        "slice_to_end = arr[6:]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[6:] = {slice_to_end}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "c6cda958"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Slicing with a Step: `arr[start:end:step]`\n",
        "\n",
        "This extracts elements with a specified step size within the given range."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "26b63a30"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Get every second element from index 1 to 8\n",
        "slice_step = arr[1:9:2]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[1:9:2] = {slice_step}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get every third element from the entire array\n",
        "slice_all_step = arr[::3]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[::3] = {slice_all_step}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "909d5439"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Negative Indexing for Slicing\n",
        "\n",
        "Negative indices count from the end of the array. `-1` is the last element, `-2` is the second to last, and so on."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "4be04596",
        "outputId": "4099083f-5e47-4fe0-d436-1ed36cb74e34"
      },
      "source": [
        "specific_slice = arr[2:6]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[2:6] = {specific_slice}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": 6,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "arr[2:6] = [30 40 50]\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "23ef58c3"
      },
      "source": [
        "# Get the last 3 elements\n",
        "slice_neg_end = arr[-3:]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[-3:] = {slice_neg_end}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Get elements from the beginning up to the third to last element\n",
        "slice_neg_start = arr[:-3]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[:-3] = {slice_neg_start}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Reverse the array\n",
        "slice_reverse = arr[::-1]\n",
        "print(f\"arr[::-1] = {slice_reverse}\")"
      ],
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": []
